subject: AArch64 support
commitMessage:
AArch64 support

Tizen toolchain team in Samsung company is planning to build Tizen
for new arm 64 bit architecture - Aarch64. But package "xf86-input-gesture"
cannot be built for this architecture because of build errors.

The problem is in debug print, so just changed format string to print a pointer.

Change-Id: Ie2a02c00592122d495baaedb34763d7b541295c2
Signed-off-by: Vyacheslav Barinov <v.barinov@samsung.com>

comments.message: Uploaded patch set 1.

Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

I can merge it , just need the verified bit
Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2
Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

Patch Set 1: Verified+1

This change does not break armv7l and i586 build and enables aarch64 build:
Patched:
https://build.tizen.org/package/show?package=xf86-input-gesture&project=devel%3Aarm_toolchain%3AMobile%3Atest
Not patched:
https://build.tizen.org/package/show?package=xf86-input-gesture-fail&project=devel%3Aarm_toolchain%3AMobile%3Atest

Patch Set 1: Verified-1 Code-Review-2

again - can you prove to me that the pointer only contains data in the lower 32bits? otherwise this breaks. its a bad hack. your fix to shut up warnings just means this bug is lost forever as no one will notice anymore!

Patch Set 1: Verified+1 Code-Review+2

oh gees. sorry - i was looking at another 64bit patch and got mixed up. never mind. approved.
Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2
Change has been successfully merged into the git repository.
